HEADWORD: Circumflexion
<hw>Cir`cum*flex"ion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of bending, or causing to assume a curved form.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A winding about; a turning; a circuity; a
fold.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Circumfluence</ent>⟦br⟧
